                h3.mb-3 Element/State Colors
                p Element colors are reserved for user interface design. Use these to help call attention to specific UI elements, such as buttons, callouts, icons, etc. The element colors adhere to WCAG 2.0 standards, and therefore are highly accessible to visually impaired and color blind users. Each element color is mapped to what we call a visual intent. We use intents to convey the status of UI elements:
                  ul
                    li Blue (intent: primary) elevates elements from the typical gray scale UI frame.
                    li Green (intent: success) indicates successful operations.
                    li Orange (intent: warning) indicates warnings and intermediate states.
                    li Red (intent: danger) indicates errors and potentially destructive operations.
